1
00:01:54,980 --> 00:01:57,180
I'm not a lonely old man.

2
00:01:58,180 --> 00:01:59,340
I'm here with my wife,

3
00:01:59,340 --> 00:02:02,500
moving into our Yangliu Xincheng together.

4
00:02:03,819 --> 00:02:05,659
Coming to this retirement community

5
00:02:05,859 --> 00:02:07,859
isn't because my children are unfilial.

6
00:02:08,699 --> 00:02:09,979
I'm just here because

7
00:02:09,979 --> 00:02:11,379
life is convenient here,

8
00:02:11,659 --> 00:02:13,060
and there's full medical care.

9
00:02:13,659 --> 00:02:14,699
Most importantly,

10
00:02:14,699 --> 00:02:15,500
everyone here

11
00:02:15,500 --> 00:02:17,180
is about my age.

12
00:02:17,740 --> 00:02:19,539
I'm here to have fun.

13
00:02:19,539 --> 00:02:20,620
About the same age...

14
00:02:20,620 --> 00:02:21,780
Having fun...

15
00:02:22,500 --> 00:02:23,340
Professor Zhu,

16
00:02:23,659 --> 00:02:26,259
so you admit you're here to have fun too.

17
00:02:27,020 --> 00:02:28,219
But that doesn't include him.

18
00:02:28,819 --> 00:02:30,060
As soon as I see him,

19
00:02:30,419 --> 00:02:31,639
I can't smile anymore.

20
00:02:31,919 --> 00:02:32,479
What?

21
00:02:32,659 --> 00:02:33,539
You're here?

22
00:02:34,500 --> 00:02:35,300
I'm leaving.

23
00:02:35,599 --> 00:02:36,699
What's going on here?

24
00:02:40,180 --> 00:02:41,099
An interview?

25
00:02:41,379 --> 00:02:42,580
Yes, field research.

26
00:02:42,580 --> 00:02:43,300
Just documenting things.

27
00:02:43,500 --> 00:02:44,460
By the way, Yusheng,

28
00:02:44,659 --> 00:02:45,879
I've been meaning to ask you.

29
00:02:46,340 --> 00:02:47,180
This place of ours...

30
00:02:47,500 --> 00:02:49,219
it's not rural farmland,

31
00:02:49,979 --> 00:02:52,560
so why do you call it "field research"?

32
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:53,620
Yeah.

33
00:02:53,620 --> 00:02:55,539
Doesn't that make us all field mice?

34
00:02:56,139 --> 00:02:57,599
And wouldn't Gou'er Ye become a field dog?

35
00:02:58,300 --> 00:03:00,000
Who are you calling a lapdog?

36
00:03:04,560 --> 00:03:05,900
Professor Fan, how did this happen?

37
00:03:05,900 --> 00:03:06,699
Here, sit down quickly.

38
00:03:07,060 --> 00:03:08,099
Is it bleeding?

39
00:03:08,099 --> 00:03:08,419
No.

40
00:03:08,419 --> 00:03:08,979
No need.

41
00:03:08,979 --> 00:03:10,180
Don't keep covering it.

42
00:03:10,180 --> 00:03:10,539
No blood.

43
00:03:10,539 --> 00:03:11,379
Just a bump.

44
00:03:11,580 --> 00:03:12,860
Gou'er Ye, you really are...

45
00:03:13,460 --> 00:03:14,180
Where is he?

46
00:03:15,740 --> 00:03:16,500
Look at that.

47
00:03:16,500 --> 00:03:17,780
That old man runs so fast.

48
00:03:18,939 --> 00:03:19,620
Understood.

49
00:03:20,659 --> 00:03:22,419
Your field research.

50
00:03:23,479 --> 00:03:24,759
Specifically...

51
00:03:24,759 --> 00:03:25,740
social research.

52
00:03:25,740 --> 00:03:26,139
Right.

53
00:03:26,259 --> 00:03:27,120
Is my understanding correct?

54
00:03:27,520 --> 00:03:28,219
Yes.

55
00:03:28,379 --> 00:03:29,419
As expected of Boss Li.

56
00:03:29,419 --> 00:03:30,699
Your comprehension is strong.

57
00:03:31,819 --> 00:03:32,819
So here's the question.

58
00:03:33,060 --> 00:03:34,340
You went to all this trouble...

59
00:03:34,340 --> 00:03:35,979
to come to our retirement community...

60
00:03:36,699 --> 00:03:38,159
to investigate us...

61
00:03:38,740 --> 00:03:39,740
what is it for?

62
00:03:40,099 --> 00:03:41,180
Survey sampling.

63
00:03:41,180 --> 00:03:42,180
Data collection.

64
00:03:42,419 --> 00:03:44,580
By analyzing your generation of seniors...

65
00:03:44,740 --> 00:03:47,180
we hope to reach a universal conclusion.

66
00:03:49,139 --> 00:03:49,939
You...

67
00:03:50,460 --> 00:03:51,580
analyze us?

68
00:03:52,539 --> 00:03:54,060
Can you understand our era?

69
00:03:54,060 --> 00:03:55,979
Have you experienced what we went through?

70
00:03:56,340 --> 00:03:57,740
I think we can.

71
00:03:57,819 --> 00:03:58,800
Because we are approaching it from...

72
00:03:58,800 --> 00:04:00,659
a sociological perspective.

73
00:04:00,939 --> 00:04:02,699
No perspective will work.

74
00:04:02,819 --> 00:04:04,180
Studying us?

75
00:04:06,060 --> 00:04:07,419
Kids these days...

76
00:04:07,620 --> 00:04:08,780
Can't carry on your shoulders...

77
00:04:08,780 --> 00:04:09,780
can't lift with your hands...

78
00:04:09,900 --> 00:04:10,939
Lazy,

79
00:04:10,939 --> 00:04:11,939
and ignorant of life's basics.

80
00:04:12,699 --> 00:04:13,500
That's not right.

81
00:04:14,020 --> 00:04:15,860
Society is always progressing.

82
00:04:15,939 --> 00:04:18,100
Each new generation surpasses the last.

83
00:04:18,100 --> 00:04:20,300
Each generation is better than the last.

84
00:04:20,860 --> 00:04:22,100
That's not necessarily true.

85
00:04:22,459 --> 00:04:24,980
Historically speaking, each generation improves.

86
00:04:25,100 --> 00:04:25,939
However...

87
00:04:26,379 --> 00:04:27,899
occasionally there are one or two generations...

88
00:04:27,899 --> 00:04:29,100
that might be exceptions.

89
00:04:29,259 --> 00:04:31,259
The West had The Beat Generation.

90
00:04:31,459 --> 00:04:32,980
Here we have the lying-flat generation.

91
00:04:33,699 --> 00:04:35,779
Lying flat is a minority, after all.

92
00:04:35,779 --> 00:04:38,100
Look at me, didn't I get up early?

93
00:04:38,459 --> 00:04:39,379
Shut up.

94
00:04:39,379 --> 00:04:41,379
You're the most unreliable one of this generation.

95
00:04:41,620 --> 00:04:42,779
You compare yourselves to us?

96
00:04:42,779 --> 00:04:43,819
How can you compare?

97
00:04:43,939 --> 00:04:44,699
The hardships we endured...

98
00:04:44,699 --> 00:04:45,500
the books we read...

99
00:04:45,500 --> 00:04:46,699
the things we experienced...

100
00:04:47,259 --> 00:04:48,540
To compare with us...

101
00:04:48,740 --> 00:04:49,819
besides playing video games...

102
00:04:49,819 --> 00:04:50,939
what else can you compare with?

103
00:04:53,459 --> 00:04:54,540
But we are young

104
00:04:55,139 --> 00:04:56,500
We have new knowledge

105
00:04:56,500 --> 00:04:57,139
New concepts

106
00:04:57,139 --> 00:04:58,100
New skills

107
00:04:58,740 --> 00:05:00,180
From intelligence to physical strength

108
00:05:00,180 --> 00:05:01,980
From explosiveness to endurance

109
00:05:02,100 --> 00:05:03,779
Then we are definitely

110
00:05:04,300 --> 00:05:05,459
stronger than you guys

111
00:05:06,019 --> 00:05:07,180
If you put it that way

112
00:05:07,579 --> 00:05:09,019
then let's have a competition

113
00:05:09,540 --> 00:05:10,939
As for the specific events

114
00:05:11,459 --> 00:05:12,920
we'll go back and think about it

115
00:05:14,180 --> 00:05:15,980
We're competing against them?

116
00:05:16,060 --> 00:05:17,759
They are all young and strong

117
00:05:18,339 --> 00:05:20,660
You didn't even discuss it with me beforehand

118
00:05:20,819 --> 00:05:22,660
Old age isn't about physical strength

119
00:05:23,060 --> 00:05:24,019
It's agreed

120
00:05:24,139 --> 00:05:26,259
We won't do those jumping and running events

121
00:05:26,459 --> 00:05:28,800
If it weren't for my head injury

122
00:05:29,420 --> 00:05:30,779
like a trivia quiz

123
00:05:30,779 --> 00:05:32,860
those youngsters definitely wouldn't beat me

124
00:05:32,860 --> 00:05:34,620
We'd win no matter what we played

125
00:05:34,620 --> 00:05:36,019
That's not necessarily true

126
00:05:36,060 --> 00:05:37,899
With Professor Fan's vocabulary

127
00:05:37,899 --> 00:05:38,899
if we compete in memorizing words

128
00:05:38,899 --> 00:05:40,699
we might not actually beat him

129
00:05:40,939 --> 00:05:43,100
Otherwise, let's compete in eating

130
00:05:43,100 --> 00:05:44,339
I don't believe that in this area

131
00:05:44,339 --> 00:05:45,420
anyone can outdo me

132
00:05:45,660 --> 00:05:46,779
Don't talk nonsense

133
00:05:46,899 --> 00:05:48,579
Old people shouldn't overeat

134
00:05:48,699 --> 00:05:49,459
Besides

135
00:05:49,620 --> 00:05:50,779
even if you really won

136
00:05:50,779 --> 00:05:51,779
that would only prove

137
00:05:51,779 --> 00:05:53,420
that our generation are all foodies

138
00:05:53,819 --> 00:05:55,199
Competing in talents and skills

139
00:05:55,540 --> 00:05:57,019
We're not sloppy about that either

140
00:05:57,180 --> 00:05:59,300
I've been a star performer since I was little

141
00:05:59,980 --> 00:06:02,540
Recitation, clapper talk, crosstalk, three-and-a-half sentences

142
00:06:02,819 --> 00:06:04,439
There's nothing I can't handle

143
00:06:05,500 --> 00:06:08,100
Who wasn't a star performer?

144
00:06:08,180 --> 00:06:11,300
I seriously learned the ukulele before third grade

145
00:06:11,300 --> 00:06:13,500
No issues other than it sounding terrible

146
00:06:14,180 --> 00:06:15,939
I could dance when I was little too

147
00:06:15,939 --> 00:06:18,459
They always put me in the front row for welcoming guests

148
00:06:18,540 --> 00:06:19,339
That...

149
00:06:19,500 --> 00:06:21,540
Beautiful flowers are blooming

150
00:06:24,100 --> 00:06:25,259
My arms and legs are old now

151
00:06:25,259 --> 00:06:26,060
It's a bit lacking

152
00:06:26,060 --> 00:06:26,699
This won't work anymore

153
00:06:26,699 --> 00:06:29,500
I also learned a couple of hometown opera pieces as a kid

154
00:06:29,500 --> 00:06:31,100
It's just been a long time since I sang

155
00:06:31,100 --> 00:06:32,459
I've forgotten it all

156
00:06:32,819 --> 00:06:33,620
Alright

157
00:06:33,939 --> 00:06:35,699
These can all be competition events

158
00:06:35,939 --> 00:06:36,959
I...

159
00:06:37,500 --> 00:06:40,180
I did practice piano for a few days in the past

160
00:06:40,220 --> 00:06:42,459
but I've forgotten most of it now

161
00:06:42,660 --> 00:06:43,620
It's okay

162
00:06:43,699 --> 00:06:45,060
You can brush up on it

163
00:06:45,060 --> 00:06:45,860
It'll surely work

164
00:06:46,100 --> 00:06:46,899
Okay

165
00:06:47,180 --> 00:06:48,220
You count as one entry

166
00:06:48,540 --> 00:06:50,060
I'll bring out my treasured masterpiece

167
00:06:50,060 --> 00:06:51,620
Dingjun Shan, and show it off to them

168
00:06:51,819 --> 00:06:53,819
Let these kids really experience

169
00:06:53,899 --> 00:06:56,220
the profoundness of our traditional Chinese culture

170
00:06:56,740 --> 00:06:57,500
Yingzi

171
00:06:57,500 --> 00:06:58,139
how about you?

172
00:06:59,819 --> 00:07:00,620
Me?

173
00:07:01,300 --> 00:07:03,139
I really don't have any talents

174
00:07:03,220 --> 00:07:05,180
I just studied hard growing up

175
00:07:06,259 --> 00:07:06,980
Oh, right

176
00:07:06,980 --> 00:07:09,699
I entered a typing contest in middle school

177
00:07:09,860 --> 00:07:11,240
At the time, I won an

178
00:07:11,240 --> 00:07:12,120
eighth prize

179
00:07:13,220 --> 00:07:14,300
That's not...

180
00:07:14,899 --> 00:07:16,360
I think that's enough

181
00:07:16,740 --> 00:07:19,379
Before the grandpas and grandmas even get to Yingzi

182
00:07:19,579 --> 00:07:20,939
it'll already be three to zero

183
00:07:21,019 --> 00:07:22,079
They'll be totally wiped out

184
00:07:23,899 --> 00:07:24,779
Children

185
00:07:25,420 --> 00:07:26,139
look here

186
00:07:26,139 --> 00:07:27,980
what can I do?

187
00:07:28,540 --> 00:07:29,660
You just rest

188
00:07:29,660 --> 00:07:32,139
You don't need to get involved personally

189
00:07:32,139 --> 00:07:32,899
Who?

190
00:07:32,899 --> 00:07:34,540
Who is pregnant?

191
00:07:35,300 --> 00:07:36,259
If you ask me

192
00:07:36,259 --> 00:07:37,300
this is enough

193
00:07:37,300 --> 00:07:39,500
We'll end the battle three to zero

194
00:07:39,500 --> 00:07:41,100
Don't say we're bullying the kids

195
00:07:41,360 --> 00:07:41,920
Right

196
00:07:42,680 --> 00:07:43,480
It's settled then

197
00:08:02,120 --> 00:08:03,339
It's getting late.

198
00:08:04,319 --> 00:08:05,560
And there's quite a crowd.

199
00:08:06,319 --> 00:08:08,120
Let's get started.

200
00:08:08,259 --> 00:08:09,220
The first match.

201
00:08:10,420 --> 00:08:11,740
The Clapper Talk duel.

202
00:08:12,300 --> 00:08:13,500
The opposing sides are...

203
00:08:13,980 --> 00:08:17,300
Zhu Zhu from the Youth Team...

204
00:08:20,319 --> 00:08:24,899
versus Mr. Liang Shengtian from the Seniors Team.

205
00:08:29,339 --> 00:08:30,139
Well then...

206
00:08:30,259 --> 00:08:31,759
I will perform a piece for everyone...

207
00:08:31,759 --> 00:08:33,179
a classic Clapper Talk...

208
00:08:33,179 --> 00:08:34,100
"Rescue from the Prison Cart."

209
00:08:34,360 --> 00:08:35,779
Great!

210
00:08:42,220 --> 00:08:42,840
Good!

211
00:08:43,799 --> 00:08:44,759
Don't clap for him.

212
00:08:45,960 --> 00:08:48,019
Why keep clicking the clappers without speaking?

213
00:08:48,279 --> 00:08:49,259
I'm about to speak.

214
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:44,000
Good!

215
00:09:44,820 --> 00:09:46,500
That was amazing! Come on.

216
00:09:48,100 --> 00:09:48,960
Let's look at our judges.

217
00:09:49,879 --> 00:09:50,519
Come on.

218
00:09:50,519 --> 00:09:52,840
After a unanimous decision by our judges...

219
00:09:53,080 --> 00:09:54,320
for this Youth-Senior competition...

220
00:09:54,320 --> 00:09:56,000
the first round of Clapper Talk...

221
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:58,159
the winner is, from the Seniors Team...

222
00:09:58,159 --> 00:09:59,399
Mr. Liang Shengtian!

223
00:10:00,539 --> 00:10:01,159
Yay!

224
00:10:03,320 --> 00:10:04,440
Let me say a few words.

225
00:10:04,600 --> 00:10:06,960
I think this young man is quite good.

226
00:10:07,200 --> 00:10:08,240
He plays the clappers well.

227
00:10:08,240 --> 00:10:11,240
The key is he dared to choose this old piece.

228
00:10:11,399 --> 00:10:12,799
And his lyrics were rock solid.

229
00:10:12,799 --> 00:10:13,960
A real talent.

230
00:10:14,759 --> 00:10:15,639
I propose...

231
00:10:15,879 --> 00:10:18,679
that we both be tied for champion in this match.

232
00:10:19,480 --> 00:10:21,440
Great!

233
00:10:24,080 --> 00:10:24,799
Uncle Liang...

234
00:10:24,799 --> 00:10:26,039
you were really awesome too.

235
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:27,440
Still going strong.

236
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:30,159
It's a tie!

237
00:10:33,019 --> 00:10:34,600
Now, next is the intense...

238
00:10:34,600 --> 00:10:35,740
second round of competition.

239
00:10:35,740 --> 00:10:37,700
First up is our...

240
00:10:37,700 --> 00:10:38,899
beloved, respected...

241
00:10:38,899 --> 00:10:40,100
and adorable Boss Li...

242
00:10:40,220 --> 00:10:42,919
Mr. Li Jianguo!

243
00:10:43,639 --> 00:10:44,700
Boss Li!

244
00:10:44,799 --> 00:10:45,600
Go for it!

245
00:10:45,700 --> 00:10:46,120
Boss Li!

246
00:10:48,240 --> 00:10:49,039
Go for it!

247
00:10:51,980 --> 00:10:53,340
I'll do my humble best then.

248
00:10:54,100 --> 00:10:56,019
I'll sing a piece of traditional Peking Opera...

249
00:10:56,019 --> 00:10:56,899
"Dingjun Shan."

250
00:10:56,899 --> 00:10:57,659
Good!

251
00:10:59,460 --> 00:11:00,179
See that?

252
00:11:00,179 --> 00:11:01,259
He's got the moves.

253
00:11:41,799 --> 00:11:44,759
Bravo!

254
00:11:44,759 --> 00:11:46,059
This is a true traditional treasure.

255
00:11:46,059 --> 00:11:48,700
Exactly. You've secured the score for this round.

256
00:11:49,659 --> 00:11:51,539
Grandpa Li has profound skills.

257
00:11:51,539 --> 00:11:52,700
He sang really well.

258
00:11:53,100 --> 00:11:55,700
I'll also learn from his example...

259
00:11:55,779 --> 00:11:57,620
and sing a piece of traditional treasure...

260
00:11:57,620 --> 00:11:58,480
Henan Opera...

261
00:11:58,480 --> 00:12:00,019
"Mu Guiying Takes Command."

262
00:12:00,019 --> 00:12:01,940
Good! Go Xiao Xin!

263
00:12:02,379 --> 00:12:03,179
Go Xiao Xin!

264
00:12:03,179 --> 00:12:04,139
Let's go!

265
00:12:04,139 --> 00:12:05,259
Let's go-go!

266
00:12:11,460 --> 00:12:12,179
See that?

267
00:12:12,179 --> 00:12:13,299
We've got the moves too.

268
00:12:58,679 --> 00:12:59,820
Bravo!

269
00:12:59,960 --> 00:13:02,940
Xiao Xin!

270
00:13:02,940 --> 00:13:06,460
Boss Li! Xiao Xin!

271
00:13:06,519 --> 00:13:08,440
Boss Li!

272
00:13:08,460 --> 00:13:10,039
Everyone, please settle down.

273
00:13:10,039 --> 00:13:11,159
Everyone, please settle down.

274
00:13:11,759 --> 00:13:12,600
Auntie Xiao Cai.

275
00:13:15,419 --> 00:13:17,399
As everyone has seen,

276
00:13:18,179 --> 00:13:19,659
these are different genres.

277
00:13:19,779 --> 00:13:21,500
The performance levels are both excellent.

278
00:13:22,519 --> 00:13:23,820
You're making it for us judges...

279
00:13:24,379 --> 00:13:25,580
very hard to judge.

280
00:13:26,580 --> 00:13:27,500
I think...

281
00:13:27,500 --> 00:13:28,419
our Boss Li was still...

282
00:13:28,419 --> 00:13:29,940
just a tiny, little bit better.

283
00:13:30,340 --> 00:13:31,059
Why do I feel like...

284
00:13:31,059 --> 00:13:33,539
our Xiao Xin won by a narrow margin?

285
00:13:33,580 --> 00:13:34,580
I think Peking Opera...

286
00:13:34,580 --> 00:13:35,460
is a cut above.

287
00:13:35,460 --> 00:13:36,039
National quintessence.

288
00:13:36,039 --> 00:13:36,539
That's right.

289
00:13:36,539 --> 00:13:38,740
Doesn't Henan Opera count as National quintessence?

290
00:13:39,299 --> 00:13:40,179
It counts too.

291
00:13:40,179 --> 00:13:41,000
But the singing...

292
00:13:41,240 --> 00:13:41,820
is still not...

293
00:13:41,820 --> 00:13:42,899
They were both wonderful!

294
00:13:42,899 --> 00:13:43,860
They are both National quintessence.

295
00:13:44,740 --> 00:13:46,100
What is the most commendable thing?

296
00:13:46,100 --> 00:13:47,820
It's that a young Gen Z girl

297
00:13:48,019 --> 00:13:49,539
can also love the classics

298
00:13:49,740 --> 00:13:50,820
and respect tradition.

299
00:13:50,820 --> 00:13:51,700
This is also...

300
00:13:51,940 --> 00:13:52,940
truly praiseworthy.

301
00:13:52,940 --> 00:13:53,700
Isn't it?

302
00:13:54,139 --> 00:13:55,620
I'll follow Comrade Old Liang's example.

303
00:13:56,059 --> 00:13:56,940
I suggest...

304
